issues.description: The problem statement / task specifies that ExcellenceLand has a private attribute 'rides' of type List<Ride> and asks for public getters for all attributes. In the solution ExcellenceLand the attribute is indeed declared as List<Ride> but the public getter getRides() returns java.util.Set<Ride> (a HashSet) instead of returning a List<Ride>. This is a return-type mismatch for the getter and violates the stated attribute type in the problem description; it can confuse students about the expected type and will cause tests that expect a List<Ride> getter to fail.
issues.suggested_fix: Make the getter for rides return List<Ride> to match the attribute type specified in the task/problem. For example, change the signature to 'public List<Ride> getRides()' and return a defensive copy such as 'return new ArrayList<>(rides);' or an unmodifiable list via 'Collections.unmodifiableList(rides);'. This keeps the attribute type and the public API consistent with the problem statement.
